                                                                                                                                    IIMC hikes course fee

     A STAFF REPORTER
               
	The Indian Institute of Management (IIM) Calcutta has raised the annual fee for its flagship two-year postgraduate diploma course from Rs 2 lakh to Rs 3 lakh. 
    
	Facility upgrade, campus upkeep and possible increase in faculty salary have prompted the decision by the institutes board of governors.
    
	IIM Ahmedabad and Bangalore, too, have hiked the annual fees of the postgraduate diploma course.
    
	From the next academic year, applicants with family income below Rs 4 lakh per year will be eligible for the Joka institutes scholarships.
    
